        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "The filesystem storage adapter is using umask to set file and directory permissions.\r\n\r\nhttp:\/\/php.net\/manual\/function.umask.php\r\n{quote}\r\nNote:\r\n\r\nAvoid using this function in multithreaded webservers. It is better to change the file permissions with chmod() after creating the file. Using umask() can lead to unexpected behavior of concurrently running scripts and the webserver itself because they all use the same umask. \r\n{quote}\r\n\r\nSo on multithreaded webservers it's required to set the permissions after the file has been created and only reset a changed umask if the umask didn't changed again.\r\nBecause it's not possible to autodetect multithreaded webserver environments it have to be configurable and should be enabled by default to work well by default.\r\n\r\nAdditionally it should be enough to configure one umask (instead of split file \/ directory umask):\r\numask = 022\r\n$dirPerm  = 511 & ~$umask = 0744\r\n$filePerm = 438 & ~$umask = 0644"
        },
